@Jim 

It's an old salesman trick.  When trying to make an appointment one asks, "Would Tuesday morning or Thursday afternoon be better for you" instead of "when can we meet?". 

I lead with the assumption that the person *will* vote and just needs to express their plan.   I've found it very effective and I can't count the number of times I've guided voters through the process.

